           <h4>
               After having generations of teachers in my family, it was inevitable for me to choose a carrier other than teaching. I began teaching at an early age and reflecting back I am never ever disappointed for having to choose this one. The year 1991 saw the birth of Young Hearts where I could put my ideals for a sound and effective education in the most positive manner possible.<br><br>
The values that we try to inculcate in every child and mold these small minds into a mighty personality are truly one of the things that keep us going. In spite of the colossal task that lies underneath to run a school, the joy that we get in seeing our students coming back to us even after 20 years to thank us in making them what they are is immeasurable.<br><br>
Young Hearts has always been a platform in encouraging each and every child, giving them opportunity to excel in each and every aspect including music, art, craft, games, public speaking etc. Thus, making them confident and better citizen, capable of adapting in every walk of life.<br><br>
Having said this, I alone would not have had accomplished my aspirations and dreams without the help of my team, colleagues' and staff. So, I would like to take this opportunity to thank all those people who have become the part of Young Hearts and helped me through all the difficulties in achieving this wonderful success.<br><br>
Hail! Young Hearter.<br><br>

